The paper discusses the application of artificial intelligence, specifically deep learning, to solve problems in fingerprinting localization solutions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of data augmentation and transfer learning, which are common techniques in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI) measurements, which are commonly used in Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.NI, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.IT.
